{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8382e4e5-5ce5-4a4d-ba04-1134446dca18","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.8**, the default test runner switched to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new, non-VSTest runner). However, 3.x still shipped the VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` could still discover tests.\n\nIn **4.x**, the VSTest compatibility layer is **no longer included**. This means `vstest.console.exe` can't discover or run your tests — it simply finds zero tests.\n\n### Your options\n\n1. **Switch your CI to the new runner** (recommended):\n   Replace `vstest.console` with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or run the test executable directly. Microsoft.Testing.Platform is already wired up.\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** if you must keep `vstest.console`:\n   ```xml\n   <Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n     <PropertyGroup>\n       <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n       <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n     </PropertyGroup>\n     <ItemGroup>\n       <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" />\n     </ItemGroup>\n   </Project>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 (`dotnet test`) is the path forward — it uses the new platform natively and requires no project changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9968674b-9cf4-4591-b9bc-d9d33e5f0a16","outputTokens":364,"requestId":"0431:119996:1CB046D:20CE320:69E836C6"},"id":"061a38a8-c358-4ddf-b774-a5e9ef027ed5","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:47:42.970Z","parentId":"fea89916-75f8-4fed-b0ba-d6336923e831"}
